<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[173,1127,1163,1502]" box="[234,473,1163,1185]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Body length: 
<quantity box="[376,469,1163,1185]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" unit="mm" value="1.55">1.55 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[173,1127,1163,1502]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
All body and legs dark. 
<emphasis box="[500,524,1192,1213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Ifr</emphasis>
lines distinct. Breadth of gena 
<quantity box="[859,951,1192,1214]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" unit="mm" value="0.06">0.06 mm</quantity>
behind 
<emphasis box="[1043,1060,1192,1213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">vi</emphasis>
, eye’s height 
<quantity box="[249,342,1220,1242]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[173,1127,1163,1502]" box="[234,834,1249,1271]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Abdomen. Abdominal sternites are surprisingly narrow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[173,1127,1163,1502]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis box="[234,376,1278,1299]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Generally of a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Richards" authorityYear="1973" box="[554,660,1279,1300]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Bentrovata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[554,660,1279,1300]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Bentrovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[669,719,1279,1300]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">type</typeStatus>
. Ventro-medial process of synsternite (
<figureCitation box="[181,292,1307,1329]" captionStart="Figs 30–37" captionStartId="11.[174,219,1415,1437]" captionTargetBox="[175,1095,760,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-220@11.[174,1096,758,1393]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 30–37. Bentrovata minor sp. n., holotype male, terminalia and genitalia. 30 = dorsal part of synsternite, anterior view; 31 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 32 = ventro-medial part of synsternite, ventral view; 33 = ventral part of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 34 = surstylus, lateral view; 35 = same, ventral view; 36= hypandrium, ventral view; 37 = left postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 30; 0.2 mm for Figs 31, 33, 36; 0.1 mm for Figs 32, 34–35, 37" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946039/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Figs 31–32</figureCitation>
) with strong, black thorns/pegs in 1 row, 16 (8+8) pegs are to be counted. Dorsal part of synsternite (
<figureCitation box="[386,459,1336,1358]" captionStart="Figs 30–37" captionStartId="11.[174,219,1415,1437]" captionTargetBox="[175,1095,760,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-220@11.[174,1096,758,1393]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 30–37. Bentrovata minor sp. n., holotype male, terminalia and genitalia. 30 = dorsal part of synsternite, anterior view; 31 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 32 = ventro-medial part of synsternite, ventral view; 33 = ventral part of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 34 = surstylus, lateral view; 35 = same, ventral view; 36= hypandrium, ventral view; 37 = left postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 30; 0.2 mm for Figs 31, 33, 36; 0.1 mm for Figs 32, 34–35, 37" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946039/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) short. Pseudocerci (
<figureCitation box="[686,760,1336,1358]" captionStart="Figs 30–37" captionStartId="11.[174,219,1415,1437]" captionTargetBox="[175,1095,760,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-220@11.[174,1096,758,1393]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 30–37. Bentrovata minor sp. n., holotype male, terminalia and genitalia. 30 = dorsal part of synsternite, anterior view; 31 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 32 = ventro-medial part of synsternite, ventral view; 33 = ventral part of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 34 = surstylus, lateral view; 35 = same, ventral view; 36= hypandrium, ventral view; 37 = left postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 30; 0.2 mm for Figs 31, 33, 36; 0.1 mm for Figs 32, 34–35, 37" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946039/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) indistinct. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1118,1336,1358]" captionStart="Figs 30–37" captionStartId="11.[174,219,1415,1437]" captionTargetBox="[175,1095,760,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-220@11.[174,1096,758,1393]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 30–37. Bentrovata minor sp. n., holotype male, terminalia and genitalia. 30 = dorsal part of synsternite, anterior view; 31 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 32 = ventro-medial part of synsternite, ventral view; 33 = ventral part of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 34 = surstylus, lateral view; 35 = same, ventral view; 36= hypandrium, ventral view; 37 = left postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 30; 0.2 mm for Figs 31, 33, 36; 0.1 mm for Figs 32, 34–35, 37" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946039/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) Y-shaped, apodeme medium-long. Surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[666,780,1364,1387]" captionStart="Figs 30–37" captionStartId="11.[174,219,1415,1437]" captionTargetBox="[175,1095,760,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-220@11.[174,1096,758,1393]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 30–37. Bentrovata minor sp. n., holotype male, terminalia and genitalia. 30 = dorsal part of synsternite, anterior view; 31 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 32 = ventro-medial part of synsternite, ventral view; 33 = ventral part of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 34 = surstylus, lateral view; 35 = same, ventral view; 36= hypandrium, ventral view; 37 = left postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 30; 0.2 mm for Figs 31, 33, 36; 0.1 mm for Figs 32, 34–35, 37" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946039/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Figs 34–35</figureCitation>
) short, with only 1 strong, comparatively short ventral thorn. Distiphallus (
<figureCitation box="[648,720,1393,1416]" captionStart="Figs 30–37" captionStartId="11.[174,219,1415,1437]" captionTargetBox="[175,1095,760,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-220@11.[174,1096,758,1393]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 30–37. Bentrovata minor sp. n., holotype male, terminalia and genitalia. 30 = dorsal part of synsternite, anterior view; 31 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 32 = ventro-medial part of synsternite, ventral view; 33 = ventral part of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 34 = surstylus, lateral view; 35 = same, ventral view; 36= hypandrium, ventral view; 37 = left postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 30; 0.2 mm for Figs 31, 33, 36; 0.1 mm for Figs 32, 34–35, 37" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946039/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) medium-long and less broad than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="2021" box="[175,307,1422,1444]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Bentrovata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavithorax">
<emphasis box="[175,307,1422,1444]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">B. flavithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Postgonite (
<figureCitation box="[448,521,1422,1444]" captionStart="Figs 30–37" captionStartId="11.[174,219,1415,1437]" captionTargetBox="[175,1095,760,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-220@11.[174,1096,758,1393]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 30–37. Bentrovata minor sp. n., holotype male, terminalia and genitalia. 30 = dorsal part of synsternite, anterior view; 31 = sternite 5 and ventral part of synsternite, ventral view; 32 = ventro-medial part of synsternite, ventral view; 33 = ventral part of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite, caudal view; 34 = surstylus, lateral view; 35 = same, ventral view; 36= hypandrium, ventral view; 37 = left postgonite, phallus and phallapodeme, lateral view. Scale: 0.4 mm for Fig. 30; 0.2 mm for Figs 31, 33, 36; 0.1 mm for Figs 32, 34–35, 37" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4946039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4946039/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) long, slender, slightly curved, with a gently proclinate, blunt apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[173,1127,1163,1502]" box="[234,437,1480,1502]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
